   424	
   425	## 7. Environment Variables Reference
   426	
   427	| Variable | Required | Where to Get It | Example (redacted) |
   428	|----------|----------|-----------------|-------------------|
   429	| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` | Required | Supabase > Project Settings > API > Project URL | `https://abcdefgh.supabase.co` |
   430	| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | Required | Supabase > Project Settings > API > anon key | `eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...` |
   431	| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | Required | Supabase > Project Settings > API > service_role key | `eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...` |
   432	| `INNGEST_EVENT_KEY` | Required | Inngest > Settings > Event Keys | `event_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX` |
   433	| `INNGEST_SIGNING_KEY` | Required | Inngest > Settings > Signing Keys | `signkey-prod-XXXXXXXX` |
   434	| `RESEND_API_KEY` | Required | Resend > API Keys | `re_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX` |
   435	| `RESEND_FROM_EMAIL` | Required | Your verified Resend domain | `noreply@robertoscrigna.com` |
   436	| `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` | Required | Your Vercel deployment URL | `https://roberto-scrigna.vercel.app` |
   437	| `CHROMIUM_PATH` | Optional | Leave empty on Vercel; set to local Chrome path for development only | `/Applications/Google Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google Chrome` |
   438	
   439	Notes:
   440	
   441	- Variables prefixed `NEXT_PUBLIC_` are embedded into the client-side JavaScript
   442	  bundle at build time. Never put secrets in `NEXT_PUBLIC_` variables.
   443	- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` bypasses all Row Level Security policies. It is used only
   444	  in `src/lib/inngest/functions.ts` for background jobs that need to read/write across
   445	  clients. Keep it server-side only.
   446	- `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` is used to construct absolute URLs in emails (e.g. portal links,
   447	  magic links, check-in links). If this is wrong, links in emails will point to the
   448	  wrong host. Set it to the canonical production URL without a trailing slash.
   449	
   450	---
   451	
   452	## 8. Troubleshooting
   453	
   454	### PDF Generation Fails or Times Out
   455	
   456	**Symptom:** Clicking "Download PDF" returns a 500 error or times out after 10 seconds.
   457	
   458	**Cause 1 — Function timeout too short.** The Hobby plan enforces a 10-second limit.
   459	PDF generation with `@sparticuz/chromium` typically takes 12-20 seconds on a cold start.
   460	
   461	**Fix:** Upgrade to Vercel Pro and set the max duration to 60 seconds on the PDF routes
   462	(see Section 5.2). Warm invocations are faster (~3-5s) but you still need headroom for
   463	cold starts.
   464	
   465	**Cause 2 — `CHROMIUM_PATH` set incorrectly on Vercel.** If `CHROMIUM_PATH` is set to
   466	a local path like `/Applications/Google Chrome.app/...`, Vercel will try to launch a
   467	binary that does not exist in the serverless container.
   468	
   469	**Fix:** Delete the `CHROMIUM_PATH` environment variable from Vercel entirely. The
   470	generator detects `process.env.VERCEL` automatically and uses
   471	`chromium.executablePath()` from `@sparticuz/chromium`.
   472	
   473	**Cause 3 — Missing `@sparticuz/chromium` bundle.** If the dependency was removed from
   474	`package.json`, Vercel will not bundle the Chromium binary.
   475	
   476	**Fix:** Confirm `@sparticuz/chromium` is present in `dependencies` (not
   477	`devDependencies`) in `package.json`.
   478	
   479	---
   480	
   481	### Emails Are Not Sending
   482	
   483	**Symptom:** Plan delivery emails, magic links, or check-in links never arrive. No
   484	error is thrown in the app.
   485	
   486	**Cause 1 — `RESEND_API_KEY` is wrong or missing.** The Resend client in
   487	`src/lib/resend/client.ts` initialises with `process.env.RESEND_API_KEY`. If the key
   488	is missing, the SDK silently fails on some versions.
   489	
   490	**Fix:** Verify the key is set in Vercel environment variables. Check the Resend
   491	dashboard under **Logs** to confirm whether requests are reaching Resend at all.
   492	
   493	**Cause 2 — Sending domain is not verified.** Resend rejects emails from unverified
   494	domains.
   495	
   496	**Fix:** Go to Resend > Domains. The domain used in `RESEND_FROM_EMAIL` must show
   497	status **Active**. If it shows **Pending**, the DNS records have not propagated yet.
   498	
   499	**Cause 3 — `RESEND_FROM_EMAIL` uses a domain not listed in Resend.** The FROM address
   500	must exactly match a verified domain (including subdomain, if applicable).
   501	
   502	**Fix:** If `RESEND_FROM_EMAIL` is `noreply@mail.robertoscrigna.com`, you must verify
   503	`mail.robertoscrigna.com` (the full sending domain), not just `robertoscrigna.com`.
   504	
   505	---
   506	
   507	### Inngest Functions Are Not Firing
   508	
   509	**Symptom:** Background jobs (email notifications, weight alerts, etc.) never execute.
   510	No runs appear in the Inngest dashboard.
   511	
   512	**Cause 1 — Endpoint not registered.** If you skipped Section 3.3, Inngest does not
   513	know where to send work.
   514	
   515	**Fix:** Go to Inngest > Apps and register `https://your-app.vercel.app/api/inngest`.
   516	Inngest will perform a `GET` to that URL to discover functions. Confirm the response
   517	includes all 12 functions.
   518	
   519	**Cause 2 — `INNGEST_SIGNING_KEY` mismatch.** If the signing key in Vercel does not
   520	match the one in Inngest, payloads will fail signature verification and be rejected.
   521	
   522	**Fix:** Regenerate the signing key in Inngest, update `INNGEST_SIGNING_KEY` in Vercel,
   523	and redeploy.
   524	
   525	**Cause 3 — `INNGEST_EVENT_KEY` missing.** Events are sent from the app using the event
   526	key. Without it, events are sent unauthenticated and may be rejected.
   527	
   528	**Fix:** Confirm `INNGEST_EVENT_KEY` is set in Vercel and matches the key shown in the
   529	Inngest dashboard.
   530	
   531	---
   532	
   533	### Client Portal Shows 404 or Access Denied
   534	
   535	**Symptom:** A client clicks the portal link from their email and sees a 404, a blank
   536	page, or an "access denied" error after logging in.
   537	
   538	**Cause 1 — Client has no `auth_user_id`.** The `client` table has a nullable
   539	`auth_user_id` column. If a client was created without triggering the auth user
   540	creation flow, the column is NULL and their session cannot be linked to their record.
   541	
   542	**Fix:** In the Supabase SQL Editor, find the client:
   543	
   544	```sql
   545	SELECT id, full_name, email, auth_user_id FROM client WHERE email = 'client@email.com';
   546	```
   547	
   548	If `auth_user_id` is NULL, create an auth user for them via the Supabase Authentication
   549	dashboard, copy the resulting UID, and update the client record:
   550	
   551	```sql
   552	UPDATE client SET auth_user_id = '<auth_user_uid>' WHERE id = '<client_id>';
   553	```
   554	
   555	**Cause 2 — Portal URL is wrong.** Check that `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` is set to the
   556	correct production URL. If it points to `localhost:3000`, portal links in emails will
   557	redirect clients to a local address that does not exist from their machine.
   558	
   559	**Cause 3 — Client is logging in with the partner login, not the portal login.** The
   560	app has two separate auth entry points. If a client uses the main `/auth` route
   561	(partner login), they will not find a partner record and will see an error.
   562	
   563	**Fix:** Ensure email links point to `/portal/login`, not the root login page.
   564	
   565	---
   566	
   567	### RLS Migration Error: "relation does not exist"
   568	
   569	**Symptom:** Running the migration SQL returns an error like
   570	`ERROR: relation "partner" does not exist`.
   571	
   572	**Cause:** The SQL editor may have run a partial statement due to a timeout or a
   573	syntax-highlighting issue.
   574	
   575	**Fix:** Run the migration in smaller chunks. The schema is structured with clear
   576	comment separators (`-- ── ... ──`). Run the Extensions block first, then each table
   577	block, then the RLS block, then the trigger block. Each section is independent except
   578	that RLS policies must be run after the tables exist, and triggers must be last.
   579	
   580	---
   581	
   582	### Build Fails: Type Errors or Missing Modules
   583	
   584	**Symptom:** Vercel build log shows TypeScript errors or `Cannot find module` messages.
   585	
   586	**Fix — TypeScript errors:** These indicate a code issue, not a deployment configuration
   587	problem. Fix the errors locally by running `bun run build`, resolving all type errors,
   588	and pushing again.
   589	
   590	**Fix — Missing module:** Confirm the module is in `dependencies` (not
   591	`devDependencies`) in `package.json`. Vercel only installs production dependencies
   592	during build. Running `bun install` locally and pushing the lockfile sometimes resolves
   593	resolution differences between local and Vercel environments.
   594	
   595	---
   596	
